L O V E  Y O U R  H O M E
______
Would you ever walk into your home and fill it with garbage? Probably not. It is completely mind-boggling to me that whilst we have respect for our homes, a lot of people take their imprint on the planet we live on for granted by adding to the never ending problem of plastic polution. It's time to start thinking about the Planet and your effect on it. Not only for yourself, but for your children.
__
Time Taken for Waste Items to Decompose:
â–ªï¸Plastic bottles - 450 years;
â–ªï¸Plastic bags - 10 - 20 years;
â–ªï¸Cigarette Butts - 10-12 years;
â–ªï¸ Monofilament Fishing Line - 600 years;
â–ªï¸Rubber-Boot Sole - 50-80 years;
â–ªï¸Foamed Plastic Cups - 50 years;
â–ªï¸ Leather shoes - 25-40 years;
â–ªï¸Milk Cartons - 5 years;
â–ªï¸Plywood - 1-3 years;
â–ªï¸Painted board - 13 years;
â–ªï¸Cotton Glove - 3 months;
â–ªï¸Cardboard - 2 months;
â–ªï¸Styrofoam- It does not biodegrade;
â–ªï¸Nylon Fabric- 30-40 years;
â–ªï¸Tin can- 50 years;
â–ªï¸Ropes - 3-14 months;
__
What You can do...
â–ªï¸Carry a reusable bag with you and take enough for your shopping.
â–ªï¸Carry a reusable cup for your coffee.
â–ªï¸Take your own water with you so you don't have to buy a plastic bottle.
â–ªï¸Get rid of clingfilm - there are plenty of suitable alternatives.
â–ªï¸Don't use plastic straws! Paper and metal ones are now available.
â–ªï¸ Swap to soap bars to banish plastics from your basin.
â–ªï¸Go green with your cleaning - there are so many options out there but my favourites are @smolproducts for dishwasher tablets and @oceansaverdrops for all my cleaning products.
â–ªï¸Look out for plastics in your beauty regime. @upcirclebeauty products come in recyclable packaging and makes your skin glow and I've recently ordered from @desirootsbeauty which also uses recyclable packaging for their cream and thinks about all the ingredients used in their products.
__
This list isn't exhaustive but are some easier ways to make an impact on your plastic use. Life is about changing - nothing ever stays the same. And anyway, great things never came from comfort zones.
__
